Let $$A,B,C,D,E,F$$ be six points on a non-degenerate [[conic|Projective conic]]. Then the intersection points of opposite sides of the hexagon $$ABCDEF$$ lie on a line.

The [[dual|Dual projective space]] of this is known as [[Brianchon's theorem]].